description: {"blocks":[{"key":"fn7db","text":"This protocol describes the use of Deterministic Barcoding in Tissue for spatial omics sequencing (DBiT-seq) platform to construct a multi-omics atlas on fixed frozen tissue samples. This approach uses a microfluidic-based method to introduce combinatorial DNA oligo barcodes directly to the cells in a tissue section fixed on a glass slide. This technique does not directly resolve single cells but can achieve a near-single-cell resolution for spatial transcriptomics and spatial analysis of a targeted panel of proteins.
